<TITLE> Bangladesh 217-7 at tea </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 18 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh went to tea on 217 for seven on the second day of the second and final Test against West Indies at the National Cricket Stadium in St George's, Grenada on Saturday. Mushfiqur Rahim was batting on 47 while Mahmudullah Riyad was 15 not out. The eighth-wicket pair had added an invaluable 60 runs after the tourists had slumped to 157-7 in response to the home side's 237 on the opening day. The Tigers, who were reeling at lunch 134-5, lost two more wickets in the session. Raquibul Hasan's patient knock of 44 off 103 balls was ended by Kemar Roach after he featured in a 44-run stand with Bangladesh wicketkeeper-batsman Rahim. Seven runs later, stand-in-captain Shakib-Al-Hasan was Roach's third victim of the day. He made just 16 before he was caught by Ryan Au
